{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I am a vicar in the Church of England."},{"time":2000,"text":"I've been a priest in the Church for 20 years."},{"time":8000,"text":"For most of that time, I've been struggling and grappling"},{"time":12000,"text":"with questions about the nature of God. Who is God?"},{"time":18000,"text":"And I'm very aware that when you say the word \"God,\""},{"time":23000,"text":"many people will turn off immediately."},{"time":26000,"text":"And most people, both within and outside the organized church,"},{"time":31000,"text":"still have a picture of a celestial controller,"},{"time":37000,"text":"a rule maker, a policeman in the sky who orders everything,"},{"time":43000,"text":"and causes everything to happen."},{"time":45000,"text":"He will protect his own people,"},{"time":49000,"text":"and answer the prayers of the faithful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53000,"text":"And in the worship of my church,"},{"time":55000,"text":"the most frequently used adjective about God is \"almighty.\""},{"time":61000,"text":"But I have a problem with that."},{"time":64000,"text":"I have become more and more uncomfortable"},{"time":67000,"text":"with this perception of God over the years."},{"time":71000,"text":"Do we really believe that God is the kind of male boss that we've been presenting"},{"time":80000,"text":"in our worship and in our liturgies over all these years?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":84000,"text":"Of course, there have been thinkers"},{"time":86000,"text":"who have suggested different ways of looking at God."},{"time":92000,"text":"Exploring the feminine, nurturing side of divinity."},{"time":97000,"text":"Suggesting that God expresses Himself or Herself through powerlessness,"},{"time":104000,"text":"rather than power."},{"time":108000,"text":"Acknowledging that God is unknown and unknowable by definition."},{"time":113000,"text":"Finding deep resonances with other religions and philosophies"},{"time":120000,"text":"and ways of looking at life as part of what is a universal and global search for meaning."},{"time":128000,"text":"These ideas are well known in liberal academic circles,"},{"time":133000,"text":"but clergy like myself have been reluctant to air them,"},{"time":139000,"text":"for fear of creating tension and division in our church communities,"},{"time":145000,"text":"for fear of upsetting the simple faith of more traditional believers."},{"time":152000,"text":"I have chosen not to rock the boat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159000,"text":"Then, on December 26th last year, just two months ago,"},{"time":163000,"text":"that underwater earthquake triggered the tsunami."},{"time":168000,"text":"And two weeks later, Sunday morning, 9th of January,"},{"time":173000,"text":"I found myself standing in front of my congregation --"},{"time":176000,"text":"intelligent, well meaning, mostly thoughtful Christian people --"},{"time":182000,"text":"and I needed to express, on their behalf, our feelings and our questions."},{"time":190000,"text":"I had my own personal responses, but I also have a public role,"},{"time":197000,"text":"and something needed to be said."},{"time":199000,"text":"And this is what I said."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205000,"text":"Shortly after the tsunami I read a newspaper article"},{"time":208000,"text":"written by the Archbishop of Canterbury -- fine title --"},{"time":211000,"text":"about the tragedy in Southern Asia."},{"time":217000,"text":"The essence of what he said was this:"},{"time":220000,"text":"the people most affected by the devastation and loss of life"},{"time":225000,"text":"do not want intellectual theories about how God let this happen."},{"time":231000,"text":"He wrote, \"If some religious genius did come up with an explanation"},{"time":237000,"text":"of exactly why all these deaths made sense,"},{"time":243000,"text":"would we feel happier, or safer, or more confident in God?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":250000,"text":"If the man in the photograph that appeared in the newspapers,"},{"time":253000,"text":"holding the hand of his dead child was standing in front of us now,"},{"time":259000,"text":"there are no words that we could say to him."},{"time":263000,"text":"A verbal response would not be appropriate."},{"time":266000,"text":"The only appropriate response would be a compassionate silence"},{"time":273000,"text":"and some kind of practical help."},{"time":275000,"text":"It isn't a time for explanation, or preaching, or theology;"},{"time":281000,"text":"it's a time for tears."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285000,"text":"This is true. And yet here we are, my church in Oxford,"},{"time":291000,"text":"semi-detached from events that happened a long way away,"},{"time":296000,"text":"but with our faith bruised."},{"time":299000,"text":"And we want an explanation from God."},{"time":302000,"text":"We demand an explanation from God."},{"time":308000,"text":"Some have concluded that we can only believe in a God who shares our pain."},{"time":312000,"text":"In some way, God must feel the anguish, and grief,"},{"time":318000,"text":"and physical pain that we feel."},{"time":320000,"text":"In some way the eternal God must be able to enter into the souls of human beings"},{"time":329000,"text":"and experience the torment within."},{"time":333000,"text":"And if this is true, it must also be that God knows the joy and exaltation"},{"time":339000,"text":"of the human spirit, as well."},{"time":345000,"text":"We want a God who can weep with those who weep,"},{"time":348000,"text":"and rejoice with those who rejoice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352000,"text":"This seems to me both a deeply moving and a convincing re-statement"},{"time":358000,"text":"of Christian belief about God."},{"time":360000,"text":"For hundreds of years, the prevailing orthodoxy, the accepted truth,"},{"time":366000,"text":"was that God the Father, the Creator, is unchanging"},{"time":370000,"text":"and therefore by definition cannot feel pain or sadness."},{"time":376000,"text":"Now the unchanging God feels a bit cold and indifferent to me."},{"time":380000,"text":"And the devastating events of the 20th century"},{"time":386000,"text":"have forced people to question the cold, unfeeling God."},{"time":389000,"text":"The slaughter of millions in the trenches and in the death camps"},{"time":395000,"text":"have caused people to ask, \"Where is God in all this?"},{"time":399000,"text":"Who is God in all this?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":402000,"text":"And the answer was, \"God is in this with us,"},{"time":408000,"text":"or God doesn't deserve our allegiance anymore.\""},{"time":413000,"text":"If God is a bystander, observing but not involved,"},{"time":418000,"text":"then God may well exist, but we don't want to know about Him."},{"time":422000,"text":"Many Jews and Christians now feel like this, I know."},{"time":427000,"text":"And I am among them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430000,"text":"So we have a suffering God --"},{"time":432000,"text":"a God who is intimately connected with this world and with every living soul."},{"time":438000,"text":"I very much relate to this idea of God."},{"time":442000,"text":"But it isn't enough. I need to ask some more questions,"},{"time":447000,"text":"and I hope they are questions that you will want to ask, as well,"},{"time":450000,"text":"some of you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453000,"text":"Over the last few weeks I have been struck by the number of times"},{"time":457000,"text":"that words in our worship have felt a bit inappropriate, a bit dodgy."},{"time":461000,"text":"We have a pram service on Tuesday mornings for mums and their pre-school children."},{"time":467000,"text":"And last week we sang with the children one of their favorite songs,"},{"time":471000,"text":"\"The Wise Man Built His House Upon the Rock.\""},{"time":474000,"text":"Perhaps some of you know it. Some of the words go like this:"},{"time":477000,"text":"\"The foolish man built his house upon the sand /"},{"time":480000,"text":"And the floods came up / And the house on the sand went crash.\""},{"time":486000,"text":"Then in the same week, at a funeral,"},{"time":491000,"text":"we sang the familiar hymn \"We Plow the Fields and Scatter,\""},{"time":496000,"text":"a very English hymn."},{"time":498000,"text":"In the second verse comes the line, \"The wind and waves obey Him.\""},{"time":503000,"text":"Do they? I don't feel we can sing that song again in church,"},{"time":510000,"text":"after what's happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513000,"text":"So the first big question is about control."},{"time":516000,"text":"Does God have a plan for each of us? Is God in control?"},{"time":521000,"text":"Does God order each moment? Does the wind and the waves obey Him?"},{"time":528000,"text":"From time to time,"},{"time":530000,"text":"one hears Christians telling the story of how God organized things for them,"},{"time":535000,"text":"so that everything worked out all right --"},{"time":537000,"text":"some difficulty overcome, some illness cured, some trouble averted,"},{"time":542000,"text":"a parking space found at a crucial time."},{"time":546000,"text":"I can remember someone saying this to me,"},{"time":550000,"text":"with her eyes shining with enthusiasm at this wonderful confirmation of her faith"},{"time":556000,"text":"and the goodness of God."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561000,"text":"But if God can or will do these things --"},{"time":564000,"text":"intervene to change the flow of events --"},{"time":567000,"text":"then surely he could have stopped the tsunami."},{"time":570000,"text":"Do we have a local God who can do little things like parking spaces,"},{"time":575000,"text":"but not big things like 500 mile-per-hour waves?"},{"time":579000,"text":"That's just not acceptable to intelligent Christians,"},{"time":584000,"text":"and we must acknowledge it."},{"time":586000,"text":"Either God is responsible for the tsunami,"},{"time":589000,"text":"or God is not in control."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593000,"text":"After the tragedy, survival stories began to emerge."},{"time":596000,"text":"You probably heard some of them:"},{"time":598000,"text":"the man who surfed the wave,"},{"time":600000,"text":"the teenage girl who recognized the danger"},{"time":603000,"text":"because she had just been learning about tsunamis at school."},{"time":606000,"text":"Then there was the congregation who had left their usual church building on the shore"},{"time":611000,"text":"to hold a service in the hills."},{"time":613000,"text":"The preacher delivered an extra long sermon,"},{"time":617000,"text":"so that they were still out of harm's way when the wave struck."},{"time":621000,"text":"Afterwards someone said that God must have been looking after them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629000,"text":"So the next question is about partiality."},{"time":632000,"text":"Can we earn God's favor by worshipping Him or believing in Him?"},{"time":637000,"text":"Does God demand loyalty, like any medieval tyrant?"},{"time":641000,"text":"A God who looks after His own, so that Christians are OK,"},{"time":648000,"text":"while everyone else perishes?"},{"time":650000,"text":"A cosmic us and them, and a God who is guilty of the worst kind of favoritism?"},{"time":660000,"text":"That would be appalling,"},{"time":662000,"text":"and that would be the point at which I would hand in my membership."},{"time":667000,"text":"Such a God would be morally inferior to the highest ideals of humanity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675000,"text":"So who is God, if not the great puppet-master or the tribal protector?"},{"time":682000,"text":"Perhaps God allows or permits terrible things to happen,"},{"time":686000,"text":"so that heroism and compassion can be shown."},{"time":690000,"text":"Perhaps God is testing us: testing our charity, or our faith."},{"time":695000,"text":"Perhaps there is a great, cosmic plan that allows for horrible suffering"},{"time":699000,"text":"so that everything will work out OK in the end."},{"time":702000,"text":"Perhaps, but these ideas are all just variations on God controlling everything,"},{"time":711000,"text":"the supreme commander toying with expendable units in a great campaign."},{"time":718000,"text":"We are still left with a God who can do the tsunami and allow Auschwitz."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726000,"text":"In his great novel, \"The Brothers Karamazov,\" Dostoevsky gives these words to Ivan,"},{"time":733000,"text":"addressed to his naive and devout younger brother, Alyosha:"},{"time":739000,"text":"\"If the sufferings of children go to make up the sum of sufferings"},{"time":742000,"text":"which is necessary for the purchase of truth,"},{"time":745000,"text":"then I say beforehand that the entire truth is not worth such a price."},{"time":753000,"text":"We cannot afford to pay so much for admission."},{"time":757000,"text":"It is not God that I do not accept."},{"time":760000,"text":"I merely, most respectfully, return Him the ticket.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":768000,"text":"Or perhaps God set the whole universe going at the beginning"},{"time":772000,"text":"and then relinquished control forever,"},{"time":775000,"text":"so that natural processes could occur, and evolution run its course."},{"time":780000,"text":"This seems more acceptable,"},{"time":782000,"text":"but it still leaves God with the ultimate moral responsibility."},{"time":790000,"text":"Is God a cold, unfeeling spectator?"},{"time":794000,"text":"Or a powerless lover, watching with infinite compassion"},{"time":799000,"text":"things God is unable to control or change?"},{"time":803000,"text":"Is God intimately involved in our suffering,"},{"time":807000,"text":"so that He feels it in His own being?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":813000,"text":"If we believe something like this, we must let go of the puppet-master completely,"},{"time":819000,"text":"take our leave of the almighty controller, abandon traditional models."},{"time":824000,"text":"We must think again about God."},{"time":828000,"text":"Maybe God doesn't do things at all."},{"time":833000,"text":"Maybe God isn't an agent like all of us are agents."},{"time":838000,"text":"Early religious thought conceived God as a sort of superhuman person,"},{"time":843000,"text":"doing things all over the place."},{"time":845000,"text":"Beating up the Egyptians, drowning them in the Red Sea, wasting cities, getting angry."},{"time":852000,"text":"The people knew their God by His mighty acts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856000,"text":"But what if God doesn't act? What if God doesn't do things at all?"},{"time":863000,"text":"What if God is in things?"},{"time":867000,"text":"The loving soul of the universe."},{"time":870000,"text":"An in-dwelling compassionate presence, underpinning and sustaining all things."},{"time":878000,"text":"What if God is in things?"},{"time":882000,"text":"In the infinitely complex network of relationships and connections that make up life."},{"time":888000,"text":"In the natural cycle of life and death,"},{"time":892000,"text":"the creation and destruction that must happen continuously."},{"time":898000,"text":"In the process of evolution."},{"time":900000,"text":"In the incredible intricacy and magnificence of the natural world."},{"time":906000,"text":"In the collective unconscious, the soul of the human race."},{"time":910000,"text":"In you, in me, mind and body and spirit."},{"time":917000,"text":"In the tsunami, in the victims. In the depth of things."},{"time":922000,"text":"In presence and in absence. In simplicity and complexity."},{"time":927000,"text":"In change and development and growth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":932000,"text":"How does this in-ness, this innerness, this interiority of God work?"},{"time":937000,"text":"It's hard to conceive, and begs more questions."},{"time":941000,"text":"Is God just another name for the universe,"},{"time":944000,"text":"with no independent existence at all?"},{"time":946000,"text":"I don't know."},{"time":948000,"text":"To what extent can we ascribe personality to God?"},{"time":955000,"text":"I don't know."},{"time":957000,"text":"In the end, we have to say, \"I don't know.\""},{"time":961000,"text":"If we knew, God would not be God."}]},{"cues":[{"time":964000,"text":"To have faith in this God"},{"time":966000,"text":"would be more like trusting an essential benevolence in the universe,"},{"time":972000,"text":"and less like believing a system of doctrinal statements."},{"time":976000,"text":"Isn't it ironic that Christians who claim to believe"},{"time":980000,"text":"in an infinite, unknowable being"},{"time":982000,"text":"then tie God down in closed systems and rigid doctrines?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":989000,"text":"How could one practice such a faith?"},{"time":994000,"text":"By seeking the God within. By cultivating my own inwardness."},{"time":1002000,"text":"In silence, in meditation, in my inner space, in the me that remains"},{"time":1010000,"text":"when I gently put aside my passing emotions and ideas and preoccupations."},{"time":1019000,"text":"In awareness of the inner conversation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1022000,"text":"And how would we live such a faith? How would I live such a faith?"},{"time":1028000,"text":"By seeking intimate connection with your inwardness."},{"time":1033000,"text":"The kind of relationships when deep speaks to deep."},{"time":1037000,"text":"If God is in all people, then there is a meeting place"},{"time":1041000,"text":"where my relationship with you becomes a three-way encounter."},{"time":1046000,"text":"There is an Indian greeting, which I'm sure some of you know:"},{"time":1052000,"text":"\"Namaste,\" accompanied by a respectful bow,"},{"time":1056000,"text":"which, roughly translated means,"},{"time":1060000,"text":"\"That which is of God in me greets that which of God is in you.\""},{"time":1065000,"text":"Namaste."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1070000,"text":"And how would one deepen such a faith?"},{"time":1073000,"text":"By seeking the inwardness which is in all things."},{"time":1076000,"text":"In music and poetry, in the natural world of beauty"},{"time":1081000,"text":"and in the small ordinary things of life,"},{"time":1084000,"text":"there is a deep, indwelling presence that makes them extraordinary."},{"time":1089000,"text":"It needs a profound attentiveness and a patient waiting,"},{"time":1096000,"text":"a contemplative attitude and a generosity and openness"},{"time":1101000,"text":"to those whose experience is different from my own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1106000,"text":"When I stood up to speak to my people about God and the tsunami,"},{"time":1109000,"text":"I had no answers to offer them."},{"time":1113000,"text":"No neat packages of faith, with Bible references to prove them."},{"time":1118000,"text":"Only doubts and questioning and uncertainty."},{"time":1123000,"text":"I had some suggestions to make --"},{"time":1126000,"text":"possible new ways of thinking about God."},{"time":1129000,"text":"Ways that might allow us to go on, down a new and uncharted road."},{"time":1135000,"text":"But in the end, the only thing I could say for sure was, \"I don't know,\""},{"time":1143000,"text":"and that just might be the most profoundly religious statement of all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1149000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}